: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Hawberk , Lord of Stapleford was born in Stapleford, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir Laurence Hauberk I of Scalford and Margaret Attelbury. He had at least 2 sons with Agnes Bernake. He died in 1376, in his hometown."},"et":{"–1376":"–1376","–1379":"–1379","–1392":"–1392","1352–1381":"1352–1381","–1358":"–1358","–Female":"Surnud","1358":"1358","1379":"1379","1376":"1376","1352":"1352","about 1352":"umbes 1352","1381":"1381","1392":"1392","Stapleford,Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stapleford, Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"–1376":"–1376","–1379":"–1379","–1392":"–1392","1352–1381":"1352–1381","–1358":"–1358","–Female":"Kuollut","1358":"1358","1379":"1379","1376":"1376","1352":"1352","about 1352":"noin 1352","1381":"1381","1392":"1392","Stapleford,Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stapleford, Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"–1376":"–1376","–1379":"–1379","–1392":"–1392","1352–1381":"1352–1381","–1358":"–1358","–Female":"Décédée","1358":"1358","1379":"1379","1376":"1376","1352":"1352","about 1352":"environ 1352","1381":"1381","1392":"1392","Stapleford,Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Angle